There are many fun spins or ways to create this app. Imagine a 'Tinder-style' way to connect with other Lil Nouns. Or an explorer to see the footprint of other Lil Nouns.

The value for the Lil Nouns community is that it helps drive further engagement within the community
column107:
enables more new people to get interested and possibly join the community as well as add a bit of value to the wider Web3 ecosystem if the dApp is used by others too.

#### Roadmap 

1. Sketch in Figma and prototype design the UI for this dApp (1 week)
2. Create the backend for the logic of how this dApp will work (1-2 weeks)
3. Build the frontend for this dApp (3 days)
4. Work and pull in data from on-chain to populate profiles (3 days)
5. Test and iterate (1 week)
6. Showcase a Lil Nouns dApp that helps Lil Nouns connect with each other based on interests and continuously iterate

I will likely have something to show by July or August.

#### Team 

Discord: DaysAndNight#0576
Background: Hobby-ish Product design and Software Buidler - I've been doing this for a couple of years non-professionally. I attend hackathons and love to build stuff. Professionally

Excited to share my proposal with you!

#### What?

I'd like to prepare a pixel coloring worksheets for selected 50 Lil Nouns.

![Lil Noun Pixel Coloring Worksheets](https://chibigirls.club/lilnouns/lilnouns1.png)

![Lil Noun Pixel Coloring Worksheets](https://chibigirls.club/lilnouns/lilnouns2.png)

Each coloring page would be then available as handy PDF file (CC0).

I'll also create a simple website with a list of all worksheets - so you can easily download them and print at home.

#### Why?

Pixel coloring pages are great for kids of all ages.

It's much more than just a fun!

**They improve:**

- Color Recognition

- Concentration

column524:
the lil way!

__Roadmap__
---------------

__1\. Start with the first Lil'Nouns Forest (at least 2000 Trees)__

2\. Have a Lil'Nounish sign on the forest to show the LilNouns have helped to plant this unique forest.

3\. Make the @greennouns community stronger!\

4\. Give updates on the results of the forest.\

5\. Build new humanitarian projects around the world with the community.\

6\. The remaining funds will be used to create something bigger. We have some exciting projects in mind for this community... stay tuned!

__Let's make the world a better Nounish place

column643:
what:"I am going to try and keep this as simple as possible since well its quite the simple idea.

# Project Details

I currently own the lilnouns.eth ENS address. I plan to allow Lilnoun owners to be able to mint lilnouns subdomains as ERC-1155 tokens via a token-gated minting strategy. The token-gating will be done to prevent anyone from gaming or collecting names that way as lilnouns continues to grow new members will have a shot at possibly obtaining a desirable name they would like. 

The 2eth will be used to extend the lilnouns.eth domain until the year 2069 and the remaining eth will be used to purchase a lilnouns via lilnouns.wtf

## Roadmap: The development for the ENS name wrapper contract is expected to be released 5/30wk
column644: as soon as that is released i can get to work on setting it up properly to allow people to mint the subdomain.lilnouns.eth\n\n## Team: Currently just me

column682: title:"Know your Community: Who are the Lil Nouns?"
column684:
what:"## Why
*To know thyself is the beginning of Wisdom - Socrates*

The Lil Nouns community is the Lil Nouns community's biggest asset.

The first step towards leveraging an asset is understanding the asset: who is in our community? What are they interested in? What do they value? Which DAOs do they participate in? What projects have they started?

The Lil Nouns community stands to benefit from a better understanding of itself:

*Informing community design and governance incentive programs*

We need to understand what the community values before deciding what to incentivize and how.

*Tell a more compelling story about the Lil Nouns community*

Robust data on what the Lil Nouns community values
column686:
and what they've accomplished can guide content & marketing initiatives designed to build the Lil Nouns brand and attract new members.

*Identify areas for improvement*

Several Lil Nouns members have expressed that they believe the community's accessibility is one of its biggest strengths. 

Right now
column687: we have no data to to evaluate how accessible (or diverse) the community actually is -- from the perspective of socio-economic status
column692:
etc. 

Better data can help us identify areas where we can take steps to enhance Lil Nouns diversity and accessibility.

## What? How?

1. Survey for Lil Nouners to share skills
column694:
and values that cannot be inferred by on-chain activity.
    - Demographics
    - Skills
    - Experiences
    - Values

*View draft survey here*: 
2. Analysis of on-chain (i.e. governance) and off-chain (i.e. Twitter) data to create an "on-chain resume" for the Lil Nouns community. Analysis will be shared through a Jupyter Notebook. Example research questions: 
- What DAOs do Lil Nouners participate in? Are they frequent voters? 
- How many Lil Nouners have created or frequently sign multi-sigs? How many write on Mirror?

3. Interview Lil Nouners to add "color" to our analysis.
    - Lil Nouners who are new to Web3
    - Lil Nouners who actively participate in DAOs
    - Lil Nouners who frequently write about Web3
    - Lil Nouners who have started Web3 companies / projects
4. Synthesize on-chain analysis
column696:
and interviews into a report published on Mirror.


## When?
Deliver final report by *June 26th.*

*Milestones*
- Complete and share analysis of survey results by *June 17th*
- Complete and share on-chain analysis enriched w/survey results by *June 20th*
- Complete and share Lil Nouner interviews by *June 23rd*

## Who?

0xsmiths#7689 is a Lil Nouner and [software engineer at Electric Capital](https://www.electriccapital.com/team/enrique-herreros-2) with extensive experience analyzing on-chain and off-chain Web3 data. Sample analysis [here](https://medium.com/electric-capital/electric-capital-developer-report-2021-f37874efea6d).

amphiboly#4329 is a LiL Nouner and co-founder of [Chainverse](https://www.chainverse.diamonds)

The many possibilities of blockchain technology will bring disruption to every aspect of life. The earlier kids understand the concepts behind it the easier they can build around it when they grow up.\\n\\nSchools normally do not provide a cutting edge when teaching kids. They miss out mostly on the really important parts of life for example how the financial
column1117: insurance or real estate system works. \\n\\nWith Lilnouns we have cute characters to teach everything blockchain related in a fun and understandable manner similar to Storybots on Netflix. \\n\\nLilnouns live on the blockchain and are the best to explain their heritage.\\n\\n\\nRoadmap\\n\\n‚Ä¢ decide on topics to educate about\\n‚Ä¢ storyboard first film / tutorial\\n‚Ä¢ produce the first animated film / tutorial as pilot\\n‚Ä¢ get feedback to build upon \\n‚Ä¢ market the film to schools and online education platforms\\n‚Ä¢ produce more films on various blockchain related topics and post via youtube etc.\\n‚Ä¢ build the Nouns brand with communicating to new people joining the space\\n\\n\\nTeam\\n\\nMy name is Mark

Have you consider how Lil Nouns would look like with a new dimension added?

Making Lil Nouns in 3D can help with nounification by adding a new layer of possibility and beauty to what is already awesome!

We propose creating 1 Lil Noun in 3D. The final 3D version of the Lil Nouns will be available in a .mp4 video with full rotation of the body
column2090: as well as high quality still images.\n\nThis is not a fast food process
column2092:
Lil Nouns will be carefully sculpted and all details will be carefully taken care of.

Here's an example of a [pixel character](https://opensea.io/assets/ethereum/0x521f9c7505005cfa19a8e5786a9c3c9c9f5e6f42/8521) from FRWC we turned into 3d:  
*(for videos check the opensea link down below)*

![Sage Celah in 3d](https://pbs.twimg.com/media/FULMWeoXoAQ50kd?format=jpg&name=small)

Final art will be minted as an ERC-721 NFT and auctioned
column2093: 50% of the proceeds of the auction will be sent back to the lilnouns treasury.\n\nWe're are really happy to make our first proposal to Lil Nouns and curious to hear the opinions about it
column2094:
feel free to reach out on Twitter or Discord (Mafriends#1731)!

#### Roadmap
After being approved we expect to deliver the 3D Lil Noun in a maximum of 3 weeks.

#### Team
The 3D Lil Nouns will be created by Ianzits
column2095:
3d artist that is part of the Mafriends collective.  
Mafriends is an art collective active since December 2020 producing original work on the NFT space as well as derivatives of other projects.  
The project we've worked together the most so far is Forgotten Runes Wizards Cult with more than 50 minted artworks in [these](https://opensea.io/collection/forgotten-runes-mafriends) 2 [different collections](https://twitter.com/MafriendsArt/status/1531347415105675274?s=20&t=U5kvsP_0BKVReo-BqzBjpQ).

\"what\":\"

Hello my name is Lil Package and i love cool socks! I threw it out awhile back on the idea of custom lil nouns socks but wanted to put that into action. So i am working to custom design 120 pairs of socks!


The socks will be crew height and featured the lil nouns logo scattered all over them. Below is a rough design of what they will look like (the logo will be scattered not just on the top sides).


I plan to have 25 small (lil)
column2804:
30 large and 25 x-large pairs. Now a couple questions might pop into your head. 1) Why only 120 pairs? 2) how would the claim process work?


1) I wanted to have more pairs produced but I also want to be sure our friends across the world can receive a pair of socks. Thus the decision was made to lower the sock count so that i could account for cost of shipping internationally. First class mail in the US will run about ~$8 pair to ship (with tracking) and the international shipping will range anywhere from $15-30 depending on location. Assuming we go half international and half here in the US shipping cost will amount to roughly ~$1830
column2805: leaving ~$1000 for production of all of the socks. This is again assuming ETH stays at $1400 that we will be able to produce this amount. It can be increased or decreased based on eth price. My time in putting all of the packages together
column2806:
mailing them out etc is free :) I love socks and lil nouns so i want to see it succeed.


2) Right now my plan is to have a mod create a process to open a ticket in the lil nouns discord where you can request a pair of socks to be shipped to wherever you'd like! This will also help show the Lil Nouners/mods how many pairs i have left to ship. If we do meet ups IRL at events like NFT NYC etc i can bring a handful there to give out as well!


Prototypes (still working on scattered design
column2807:
will post in discord once completed)



https://imgur.com/a/p80FjGj


Cheers

GM Fellow Lil Nouners ‚åê‚ó®-‚ó®


My name is Elle https://twitter.com/elle_binate
column2838: I am very passionate about proliferating Lil Nouners while doing good all at the same time. Highly inspired by necfas and mimix on their prop house round 3 proposal #655
column2839:
here is my proposal for prop house round 4 funding.


This activation will go towards orphanages that are listed on official Singapore Ministry Of Social And Family Development board. For this activation will be in talk with Children‚Äôs Aid Society
column2840:
Melrose as they are open to donation/volunteer for organizing recreational outing & activities for their children.


These orphans are mainly from:

  • from dysfunctional families and in need of shelter;
  • abused or neglected;
  • in need of care and protection;
  • under family guidance orders; and
  • in conflict with the Law.


https://www.msf.gov.sg/policies/Strong-and-Stable-Families/Nurturing-and-Protecting-the-Young/Child-Protection-Welfare/Pages/Children-and-Young-Persons-Homes.aspx


What will be done?


  1. Organize a one day recreational outing to S.E.A. Aquarium for the children
  2. A two way mini bus will be arrange to ferry the children and their care giver to/fro from the orphanage to destination
  3. Lil Nounish merch will be given to the children and their care giver as gifts (They may choose to wear it on the day of the outing)
  4. Dinner and ice-cream for the children to round off the day
  5. Photos of this event will be taken and posted on social media + Children's Aid Society's highlight + Shared with Lil Nouns


As I shared the same sentiment with necfas and mimix
column2841: I believe donations are Nounish and by having Lil Nouns extend its reach lil by lil to varies different organization around the globe
column2842: we will be able to strike and create more conversation around what is Lil Nouns and what is Lil Nouns DAO and what can it do
column2843:
this would create curiosity and eventually onboard new members/builders.



Fund Breakdown base on 2ETH

  1. 20X SEA Aquarium Tickets = 0.55ETH (Cater for 15 children + 4 care givers + myself)**
  2. Two way mini bus = 0.25ETH
  3. Lil Nounish gear = 0.6ETH (20-25 t-shirts)
  4. Dinner + ice cream = 0.6ETH


*Taking ETH as USD1
column2844:
200 for possible fluctuation

**No. of children brought on this outing depend on ETH value


Lil Nounish Gear mock up


Appreciate the read and support on this prop house proposal.

column3209:
\"what\":\"

We will build three lil nouns themed treasure hunt style puzzles using the Infinity Keys platform (my project).


In essence
column3210: treasure hunt style puzzles are incentivized
column3211: guided walkthroughs of a given project
column3213: or lore. Treasure provides the incentive to grab peoples' attention
column3214: solving the puzzle makes people feel good and a sense of accomplishment
column3215:
and working through the puzzle with others builds a sense of community that simple impressions or read-only media don't match.


Hunts - Currently
column3216: Infinity Keys hunts require the player to solve a passcode from a riddle or small game. The riddles and games are placed in social media channels and/or on Infinity Keys puzzle pages themselves (demos included in links below). They can require the player to explore a given NFT collection
column3219: and eventually will require players to conduct specific actions on-chain
column3220:
including in other games and/or metaverses.


Difficulty - If you've player Web3 treasure hunts before
column3221: you may notice that most people don't finish
column3222: and only a few stay invested to the end. Most treasure hunts are exclusive
column3223: only for a few winners. In contrast
column3224: IK treasure hunts are themed activations for many people to solve and feel a sense of accomplishment. You will notice that these puzzles tend to be significantly easier and shorter than typical treasure hunts. They are made for people to win
column3225: not get stuck. The point of the hunts is not to find a true champion
column3226:
the point is to invite people into a relevant community and share what's great. Bonus win if people join the community to talk about the hunt and the community helps them along - what a great intro to lil nouns!


Treasure - Each hunt will provide every solver with a free (minus gas) achievement NFT (1155). These Infinity Keys achievements will have copyright free art and design and include a nounish easter egg for fun. They are nice recognition for a job well done. In addition
column3228: we will take a snapshot of all players that have all three lil nounish achievements. We will then conduct a Chainlink VRF call to select a random winner
column3229: to whom lil nouns DAO will award one lil noun NFT. Achievement NFTs are not live on IK as of this submission
column3230:
but are coming in a few days so lils can check out the flow for other hunts to see what the experience will be like and what the art themes are (they are freaking rad and unlike anything I've seen in NFTs). The hunts themselves will remain open for anyone to gain the free achievements until there is a natural time to close the hunts.


Community - Activation events work better if there is community buy-in and participation. As part of the hunt
column3231: I will coordinate with the lil nouns DAO to create a small campaign around the hunts. This will include an initial set of tweets by Infinity Keys
column3232: RTs from the lil nouns account
column3233: and encouraged community support via tweet engagements (likes
column3235: RTs from lil nouns). We will also schedule a number of other co-marketing type events such as twitter spaces
column3237: and discord events where we can discuss the hunts
column3239:
and values associated with lil nouns.


Funds - Funds will be used to pay for a lil noun NFT from the faucet for the winning drawing
column3240: and additional funds will be used to offset the design
column3242: and marketing costs for IK. We are excited to demo the potential for these activations as digitally native experiences
column3243:
and we think this run can serve as a proof of concept for a larger (lil) grant proposal once we demonstrate the value of this style of hunt.


For further information about me and Infinity Keys:

-Andy Boyan: https://twitter.com/andyboyan

-IK: https://www.infinitykeys.io/

-Demo puzzles: https://www.infinitykeys.io/puzzles (I suggest notright and communitycode for super easy examples

and avalanche or gram for high challenge examples)

column3305:
Blockbuster gets replaced

by Netflix. When charities fail to innovate
column3306:
countless human beings do not receive

the help they deserve. Givosity plans to reimagine charity for the blockchain

age. We want to feed the hungry more efficiently
column3308:
and generally make the world a better place via technological and

operational innovation. We are on the precipice of a wholesale charitable

revolution.


Blockchain technology can anonymize giving and end

government intrusion into donor lists (this is more relevant in some

jurisdictions than others). It can dramatically decrease cross-jurisdictional

financial friction by increasing transaction speed (transactions can be

near-instant and happen any day
column3309:
any time). It can avoid governmental

interference and regulatory burdens that impair traditional banks. The

corruption that significantly impairs much of the world's humanitarian aid can

be largely avoided via blockchain transfers.


Perhaps most significantly
column3310:
the larger web3 ecosystem

enables the creation of revenue generation mechanisms vastly different from the

perpetual fundraising methods of traditional charities. Rather than standing

outside department stores asking shoppers for coins
column3312:
multichain NFT collections and release a native token. We can

embed charitable giving into various up-and-coming blockchains. We can create

token exchange utilities and decentralized finance applications that fund the

charity's treasury. With web3 development culture still in its early stages
column3313:
we

have a golden opportunity to make charitable giving an integral part of all web3

projects. Perhaps future web3 projects will consider it a social norm to donate

a flat three percent of profits to a designated web3 native charity such as

Givosity.


But the innovation goes beyond the blockchain. Typical

charities are governed by small groups of people with stale ideas and business

models more suited to the 19th century than the 21st. By applying the

\\\"wisdom of the crowd\\\" principle via a DAO
column3314:
we can apply diverse ideas

that enable us to both earn buy-in from Givosity contributors and achieve a

competitive advantage over traditional nonprofit firms. The innovation methods

of the internet revolution and the decentralization principles of the

blockchain revolution should
column3315: for the good of all humanity
column3316:
be applied to

charity.


As we are a legally registered 501(c)(3) nonprofit

organization
column3317:
all grants we receive and token sales we make will be completely

tax-exempt and tax-deductible in the United States. This gives us both

financial and marketing advantages over competing NFT membership projects. If

we can leverage the small amount of goodwill naturally provided to nonprofit

charity projects
column3318:
we can embed charitable giving in all corners of the web3

ecosystem
column3320:
and change the world for the good of

those who live in it.


Givosity will begin our charity efforts with an NFT

corporation (Givosity
column3321:

What is NounRalph ?

For the first time a Noun derivative NFT project reflects the life of a real person and puts it on the blockchain. The artist (Alexa Wagner) captured the life of real Ralph (her husband) in 4 phases from Toddler
column3472:
Kid and Young to Midlife until his 50th birthday.

NounRalph have been created by Munich based artist Alexa Wagner
column3473: as a tribute to Nouns. Nouns not only created the iconic square glasses everybody in the NFT space recognizes already from the distance. Nouns also introduced an identity
column3475:
government and treasury approach that is brining NFTs to a next level.



NounRalph is a collection of 99 NFTs on the Ethereum / Polygon blockchain. They are based on the CryptoRalph (first real person punks) art
column3476:
age groups and attributes. Each NounRalph has a unique set attributes showing details of real Ralph‚Äôs life (just like CryptoRalph).

So basically this is the first time a Noun derivative is based on a real person life.



NounRalph are even more special because of the iconic Noun style square glasses. For Age group Young and Midlife they are identical with the original Noun glasses (size and colors). For Age group Toddler and Kid the size has been adjusted to fit
column3477:
while the colors are still original.

The very first NounRalph creation as a 24√ó24 pixel art was similar to NounRalph #99. Which became the starting point for Age group Midlife. From there the artist worked backwards to Young
column3478:
Kid and Toddler.

As NounRalph is based on CryptoRalph also has 73 uniquely handcrafted traits. Each of them playing a role in real Ralph‚Äôs life either in a specific moment
column3480:
situation or characterizing him in that Age group.


Why we apply for prop.house funding

We strongly believe in the idea of Nouns/NounsDAO and want to support the distribution of those fundamental ideas. We would be able to leverage the CryptoRalph community to spread those news and motivate with an own NFT to increase engagement. Here some key facts about that community: 220+ Holders
column3484:
4ETH Volume on OpenSea Website with more info and links https://cryptoralph.io


How to use the funds

First we would increase the awareness with marketing activities leveraging the CryptoRalph community to increase the awareness about the basic ideas behind Nouns (e.g. building a dedicated website). To make the NounRalph more attractive we plan to introduce utility with own tokens (complying to legal regulations). Secondary sales and other revenue streams would flow into the NounRalph treasury which will be used to fund the DAO with the objective to acquire a Noun and follow a similar governance model !

column3550:
and I‚Äôm sure the Lil Nouns Community seeks this too. What if they could build an entire wardrobe collection with Nounish digital fashion pieces?

The FashionVerse wishes to allow Noun Community Holders build a Nounish Wardrobe Collection! This collection will include the following digital fashion pieces: 

  • Facial Accessory: Glasses
  • Tops: A Hoodie
  • Bottoms: Baggy Pants 

We have attached two samples for the hoodie for your reference. And here is a link to the 3D file for a detailed view - https://tinyurl.com/NounsGLBView


Additional details about the pieces:

  • They would be available as free mints for all Lil Nouns‚Äô holders (up until a TBD snapshot) on The FashionVerse website - https://www.thefashionverse.io/.
  • Every piece would be available in 3 different colors
column3551:
allowing holders to create 27 outfit combinations. 

Utilities provided by the piece:

  • 3D file 
  • AR Filters:
  • Snapchat and Video Conferencing filter for all pieces
  • Instagram and Facebook filter for the Glasses (it is not possible to create body wearable filters for instagram)
  • Metalooks: 
  • It refers to placing the digital fashion outfit on one‚Äôs picture. 
  • Users would be able to upload their pictures on the FV website and receive back the metalook in their virtual wardrobe on the website within 24 hours. 

Roadmap:

07/21/2022: Decision made on the grant.

08/11/2022: The holders will be able to mint on the FashionVerse website and have access to the forementioned utilities.

*Note: We will provide mockups and WIPs during the period of 07/21/2022 and 08/11/2022 along with detailed instructions on how the holders can claim their NFTs and get access to the utilities.

column3591:
a Philippine-based 1) guerrilla on-the-ground nouns proliferation pod & 2) experimental nounish art+film project that hopefully transitions to a nounish arts incubator DAO in the [near] future based on the nouns code+culture.


+++


The Philippines is one of the countries with high levels of crypto+NFT adoption. In a Feb 2022 survey
column3592: we ranked first for NFT ownership among 20 countries. According to an Australian info service findings
column3593: NFT adoption in the Philippines could soon reach 41.5 percent. As far as I know
column3594: there is currently no Nounish project yet based or focused in the Philippines. I have known about NounsDAO since late last year but have fallen DEEP in the nouns rabbit hole a few weeks ago and have not been able to get out since. Thus
column3595:
The Tropical Nouns Bureau.


At its core
column3596: Tropical Nouns Bureau is fueled by a deep curiosity on what nounish is and what nounish could be when transposed and woven into the rich dynamic tapestry of our local contemporary culture (with an extra focus on the arts+culture sector
column3597: both fringe & mainstream). It will operate both as an on-the-ground guerrilla proliferation pod (creating an organic build up that hopefully leads to a local nounish explosion) and an experimental art lab that eventually transitions to a nounish arts incubator DAO
column3598:
filling the role mostly held by elite art institutions & democratizing access to arts funding the nounish way!


There's already a slew of experimental art projects brewing (think: web3-distributed experimental nounish scifi film that revolves around the current mysterious proliferation of nouns artifacts; think: locally handcrafted nounish artifacts that will feature in the film & be available for auction via burn-to-redeem NFTs; think: wait
column3599:
better to save it all for the roadmap currently being drafted ;)


THIS 3 ETH ROUND IS FOR THE INITIAL ACTIVATION OF THE TROPICAL NOUNS BUREAU via:


1) FIRST WAVE OF STICKER+POSTER BOMBING / PROLIFERATION OF NOUNISH VISUALS ACROSS THE GREATER MANILA AREA (TO BE DOCUMENTED)


2) A SHORT ARTSY VIDEO \\\"ANNOUNCING\\\" THE BIRTH OF THE TROPICAL NOUNS BUREAU/THE START OF LOCAL NOUNISH PROLIFERATION; ALSO SETTING THE TONE FOR THE SPECIFIC NOUNISH FOCUS ON ARTS+CULTURE


3) INITIAL WEBSITE SETUP WITH THE (ABOVE VIDEO) AS LANDING PAGE + BASIC NOUNS OVERVIEW AND RELEVANT LINKS + ROADMAP


*We submitted this same prop to the nouns launchpad house as well. If we get both the grants (total of 5 ETH)
column3600: we'll be able to carry out items 1 and 2 more extensively & with more creative oomph
column3602:
and maybe save a little for minting costs (maybe a mirror article? non generative art NFTs?).


ROADMAP:

and via a Small Grants prop when it's ready] while this initial activations happens.

\"what\":\"

Prop house currently works via a simple plurality. Many people have written about the dangers of relying on majorities. Other voting schemes exist such as ranked choice and bicameral voting that could prove more effective at funding projects worth funding.

We would like to build a web app to experiment with ranked choice voting and bicameral voting. The app is meant as a demonstration and not a final product. The demo of ranked choice voting would allow you to pick your top 5 proposals instead of just one. The demo of bicameral voting would require that the Nouners and Lil Nouners both agree on a proposal for it to pass.

Built by woodpav at Namespace

column3978:
what:"

Prop house currently works via a simple plurality. Many people have written about the dangers of relying on majorities. Other voting schemes exist such as ranked choice and bicameral voting that could prove more effective at funding projects worth funding.

We would like to build a web app to experiment with ranked choice voting and bicameral voting. The app is meant as a demonstration and not a final product. The demo of ranked choice voting would allow you to pick your top 5 proposals instead of just one. The demo of bicameral voting would require that the Nouners and Lil Nouners both agree on a proposal for it to pass.

Built by woodpav at Namespace

"
column3979: tldr:"Ranked choice and bicameral voting experimental app"

Details:


To be able to Nounify other pfp's is something I would currently do to most of my NFT's for the other discords I am in. The goal of this prop is to make this as easy as possible; many don't have the time
column3993:
or where with all to photoshop on their own; but doesn't mean they wouldn't enjoy and use said derivative \\\"jpg's\\\". A unique aspect of Nifty Tailor is that they currently have a pipeline of communities who use or have used them in the past.


I have been in contact with Nifty Tailor to get Lil Nouns Noggles added to current collections and add collections. (specifics are not in place currently due to this being a rehashed prop from Rd.1) but MrBones has been more than helpful. Their Classic (NT-C) site is best purposed for our immediate usage as it has current infrastructure in place.

OTHER CURRENT OPTIONS :

Nounify Bot : NOUNS (auto done in twitter reply)

Nouns.center : NOUNS (files only)

Figma File : Lil Nouns (files only)

Nounify.wtf : Nouns (self done in web browser)


Talking with MrBones has been a pleasure. NT-C artist will have to adjust the noun noggles to match the collection sizing. NT-C then \\\"simply\\\" (a term us non devs use a lot to talk about backend stuff) needs to overlay the noggles on the website.

Timing:

Roughly 1 week and another 1 week to get it up on NT-C . MOST likely faster
column3994:
but why press for no reason üòâ

WHY:

To propel the meme isn't something we want to contain. to allow ourselves and others to easily Nounify their pfp's spreads the collection organically. As it spreads; to explain nouns and ethos becomes easier and easier... and so it spreads faster. Again
column3995:
my assumption is many have a FAVORITE pfp . this gives an easy way to \\\"support\\\" both projects.

column4178:
\"what\":\"

A Very Brief History of Linux OS

Linux is an operating system created by Finnish software engineer Linus Torvalds and the Free Software Foundation (FSF).

https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Linux


Like Windows and MacOS
column4179:
a Linux Distribution allows for the interface between computer users and computer devices.

https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Linux_distribution


Unlike Windows and MacOS which are proprietary systems
column4180:
Linux is an open source system under the GNU General Public License v2.

https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/GNU_General_Public_License.


Proposal Description

Our proposal is to create a Nouns OS MVP (Minimum Value Product) which will serve as a functional prototype (MVP) of the Nouns OS.


The Nouns OS project is a Linux Distribution Nouns-Themed that can be installed at any cheap computer Intel/AMD based so instead the user have a Windows or MacOS computer he can choose to

have a Nouns computer. The Nouns OS is not a simple Nouns theme but an entire Operating System installed at the computer.


With Nouns OS the user will have the choice to have a Nouns OS machine instead a Windows or MacOS machine.


The project is an attempt to encompass the entire Nouns ecosystem in an accessible
column4182:
serving as an All Things Nouns platform for the entire Nouns community as well as the entry point for building many other hardware projects.


Timeline

First Month

  • Build a prototype of the OS architecture based on the Nouns Ecosystem needs.

Second Month

  • Build a prototype of Nouns-Themed System Design following the standard Nouns design existent.


Obs: The architecture and system design can be discussed in a specific Nouns Discord channel.


Budgets

  • 1 ETH will be used to buy an old computer and cover other small costs that may be necessary to carry out compatibility and performance tests.
  • 2 ETHs will be used to pay for the full-time work on building Nouns OS MVP.


Team

defnullx - 30 years of developer experience with the following:

  • Desktop and Embedded Software development with C and Cpp.
  • Mobile Android App native development with Java and Kotlin.
  • Mobile IOS App native development with Objective-C.
  • Web App development with Javascript
column4185:
PHP plus Frameworks and APIs.
  • I had already built a Linux Distribution for Embedded Systems and for various Intel/AMD devices.


    • Conclusion

    The Nouns OS project can be the gateway to enormous possibilities in spaces not yet explored or even imagined for the Nouns community such as Desktop Client Machines
column4189:
Metaverse Platforms and much more.


The Nouns OS MVP is a small experiment using a small budget
column4190:
but it could become an immensely valuable NounsDAO derivative for the entire Nouns community.


Thank you very much for the appreciation.

defnullx

\"

column4223: message:"{\"title\":\"Lil Noun Pet - a virtual pet app for iOSüì±\"
column4227:
and I‚Äôm building Lil Noun Pet for iOS!

Prevent your Lil Noun‚Äôs slow march toward doom by providing it with food and water. Think Tamagotchi
column4228: but with Lil Nouns cc0 artwork! Each Lil Noun is randomly generated when the pet is hatched. Your pet‚Äôs appearance reflects its current state. If your pet is asleep
column4229: its eyes will be closed. If your pet dies
column4230: its eyes will be crossed out
column4231:
etc.

The key feature that I'm currently working on implementing is a HomeScreen Widget. The ultimate goal of this app is being able to see your pet Lil Noun right next to your favorite iOS apps on the HomeScreen.

Current features:

  • All traits from the Lil Nouns cc0 project included
  • Customize your UI with a unique accent color
  • Dracula theme dark mode
  • Local push notifications when your pet is close to death

In active development:

  • HomeScreen Widget

Future ideas:

  • Option to browse the Lil Nouns collection and choose an existing Lil Noun from the project as your pet
  • Step counter to encourage fitness and wellbeing whilst also exercising your Lil Noun
  • Additional game elements inspired by Tamagotchi
  • Animations and UI upgrades

This app will be free on the App Store with no in-app purchases and the code will remain publicly available on my GitHub page in perpetuity. 

The intent is to continue to iterate and add features over time to make this as accessible to the mainstream public as possible. The first basic iteration of the app is near-finished
column4232:
but I‚Äôm currently working on a HomeScreen widget to include before submitting it to the App Store for review.

I intend to continue building this in my spare time for the foreseeable future and look forward to spreading the Nounish meme on the App Store! Thanks for reading and considering my proposal.

-bobbyPossums

Project Details:

Building DAO like Nouns and ensuring that community members can easily navigate through them take a lot of work. Many individuals who join DAO still struggle to get around the community and find it challenging to get going and begin contributing.

By holding discussions with various DAO builders and contributors about how they select a DAO or create one to contribute to one
column4444:
we hope to find a solution to this.


Roadmap:

  1. Organize Twitter Space around DAOs
  2. Organize Discord Learning Sessions/AMAs collaborating with folks from the Nouns DAO.


Following are proposed sessions topics:

  1. What is a DAO? Why should we care about it?
  2. How do you choose a DAO and start contributing to it?
  3. How to start your own DAO and build a community for that?
  4. Day in the life of Noun DAO Contributor
  5. Day in the life of Noun DAO Team Member
  6. How does Noun DAO function from a team perspective?
  7. Tools required to run fully-functional DAO like Noun


Team:

We are a group of individuals who work in the top unicorns in India as founders
column4448:
and growth managers in addition to being web3 enthusiasts. This is a passionate team that emphasises the value of community and web3 and is driving significant change in this area in India.

I played around with some ideas for Spark AR filters and would like to expand on these ideas and make them even more fun to interact with and add more characters and customization options.


The team

My name is Dylan Blau; I've worked in the motion design industry for 10+ years. I have a degree in computer science and spent my late teens developing iOS apps. My knowledge about programming languages (objective-c/javascript) helps me automate animations in my day-to-day life as a motion designer but also helps me bridge the gap between coding and art.

I run a post-house/animation studio called Cross Cut Pictures. We do everything post-production-related
column4481:
AR assets for Instagram and Snapchat after getting inquiries from the team at VeeFriends.

The oh-so-popular \\\"which‚Ä¶ are you\\\" filter. The format that has been taking Instagram Reels by storm. And could potentially be the next viral hit.


Fully fleshed out 3-dimensional Lil Nouns characters made from scratch. Each Lil Noun has its unique animation triggered by a facial movement (raising eyebrows or opening mouth).

When the camera is flipped around

I‚Äôll interview 5 Lil Nouners in the community and share their answers on Mirror articles.

Lil Nouners have many things in common and it‚Äôs not hard to make friends in the community but most conversation happens on discord
column4626:
there‚Äôs people who don‚Äôt access discord often but like to read articles and text-based content.

This series of interviews will help the community to learn more about each other and to spread Lil Nouns culture for people outside our little bubble.

Questions will range from how they learned about Lil Nouns
column4627:
what are their views on NFTs and what is the craziest idea they think could get funded by Nouns or Lil Nouns DAO.

(I don‚Äôt want to give too many spoilers here because answers are usually better if the person don‚Äôt think a lot about it in advance)

The idea is to have no more than 10 questions
column4628:
so it‚Äôs interesting enough for people to read it all without taking too long

adding depth to our conversations and goals as a group.

Why?

Spreading the meme needs to be in all kinds of mediums if we want to be effective.

Audio

video and text!

expanding the reach of Lil Nouns.

Who?

Hi

column4639:
making the world more nounish.

Wen?

The interviews should be published two per week during a month

starting time depends on how long people will take to answer the questions but I expect the 5 interviews to be published before the 14th of September.

column4831:
description:"# Animated Lil Nouns Introductory Educational Video

Summary:
We want to create an animated video that takes lil nouns in a three-dimensional world. Our goal build out a story to lil nouns and make them relatable while staying true to the pixelated imagery created in the original artwork. Our primary aim to educate others about lilnounsdao and illustrate how to get involved in the dao.

Project Goals:
‚Ä¢	To provide an overview of lilnounsdao (auction
column4838:
while also highlighting and celebrating projects that are in the lilnouns ecosystem).
‚Ä¢	To create an engaging experience.
‚Ä¢	Improve marketing outreach by providing high-value content that furthers lil nouns mission of educating people on lil nouns. 
‚Ä¢	Remove confusion of selecting which funding method is best for someone to choose given their project goals.
‚Ä¢	Make audience smile.

Past Discussion:
https://discord.gg/xjARUcB3tJ  channel #lilnouns-video
https://discourse.lilnouns.wtf/t/proposal-for-animated-lil-noun-introductory-video/190

Conclusion:
Lil nouns branding has been an ongoing discussion and this proposal is a step toward delivering a brand marketing strategy built collaboratively by nounish community members in a decentralized way. This project further hones in answering the question ‚Äúwhat is lil nouns ethos?‚Äù 

Methodology

First stage: pre-production
Script and storyboard ‚Äì initial stages of the production process. Provides a better visualization and helps team members understand flow of the video as well as to improve coordination between team members.
There are two scripts in this project. For example
column4839:
atareh.eth has scripted his narration which he will record describing the educational points we want to convey to the audience. There is also scripting of the animation sequence which is later created into a storyboard sequence of shots to assist in visualizing the final results.
Modeling Scene and Characters ‚Äì Modeling complex characters where the topology assists in creating good movements for the characters. This stage will also include creation of pixel art which is later converted into to a model and then topology optimized for animation. (2-4 weeks)
Textures and materials ‚Äì Creating 2D images that are baked into the material. The largest amount of time will be in regard to materials for visual effects. (3 days to 1 week maximum for all material creation)
Rigging and Pre-animation prep: Rigging characters to optimize for performance and designed for natural movements. This can take 2 months however
column4840:
it will be significantly less because most will be completed prior to going on chain with the proposal (as pre-animation steps are completed at this point and general movements defined).

Second Stage: production
Animation: The model has gone through the pre-animation stages. Once we have staged the scene we will be able to animate out the scene. Once we reached this point
column4841: I estimate ‚Äústaging the animation of the scene‚Äù should take 1-2 weeks.\nLighting: Each scene is slightly different in regard to lighting. The scene that will take the longest to light will be scene 5. (Estimating 3 days - 1 week)\nVisual Effects (VFX) and composite: Visual effects for this project include dematerialization of lil noun and getting sucked into the computer screen
column4842: (lava) volcano erupting and fireworks. I‚Äôve already begun completing the more complex aspects of creating these visual effects so once we bring them into the scene
column4843:
it shouldn‚Äôt take longer than 1-2 weeks.

Third stage: post-production
Sound effects: 1 week (or longer if we are including the suggestion to include the dao on decision for which theme song we use. If there are revisions requested by the dao then the time will extend.
Rendering: The longest portion of this task is the rendering of the visual effects which include the lil noun being sucked into the computer
column4844: and fireworks. I estimate 1 week maximum for all rendering.\nPost- render edits: This is where we collect all of the rendered shots and compile them into scenes. From here
column4845: we will edit the shots within a scene
column4846:
then we will edit the scenes together. (1-2 weeks).
Review and final adjustments: At this point there will be very little left to do. Smaller changes to audio and editing can be made. 1 week
We also want to reserve some flexibility with the timeline to allow for interacting with the dao. We want to provide the dao with as much creative input/interaction with the builders as we can.

We‚Äôve begun compiling a list of assets that lilnoun1112 will be pixelating:
https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1SbS8O0oTyYaCdO2lG6ttCk3rD6_ROyRAehqDRKG8k0M/edit#gid=0

On screen recordings needed:
prophouse>lilnounsdao>connect
lilnouns(dot)wtf> DAO >Submit proposal
discord>lil grants> one or two sentences typed in the field saying ‚Äúwe started working on‚Ä¶etc‚Äù
discourse> we can use the discourse we made for this project and record that
lilnouns(dot)wtf> Playground

Current Progress:
You can follow progress on this live by looking in the #lilnouns-video channel under projects in the lilnouns discord. We‚Äôve blocked out scene 1 in order to show a pre video video as requested once we brought this proposal to discourse. We are currently in the animating stages for scene 1.

We‚Äôve also typed up a script that the lil nouns will perform:

List of Scenes

Scene 1 [introduction/LoL delegates and illustrating auction process]
The video begins with a lilnoun car pulling up to a lilnoun house. The lilnoun car has a bunch of nouns in it and one lil noun (lil noun pencil). The nouns are dropping off lil pencil and we follow him into the nounisouri where we meet a bunch of lil nouns who are hanging out and doing things in the nounisouri. The pencil lil noun walks into the nounisouri and starts writing about what he‚Äôs been discussing with nouns on a chalkboard while other lil nouns watch‚Ä¶ one lil noun raises his hand to ask a question.
Meanwhile
column4847: a panda lil noun sits at a table where he sips a coffee
column4848:
we follow the panda as he hops off his chair (which is oversized for him because he is lil) and he carries his coffee over to the computer where he works. He boots up the computer and opens the browser to [lilnouns(dot)wtf]. He checks the auction and see‚Äôs a lilnoun that he loves and reacts by throwing his hands up and then touching his lilnoun face/adjusting his glasses. Shots will flip between closeup of lil noun as he puts in a bid and the computer screen showing a new counter-bid[gradually speed up the shots as the time of the auction runs out]. As the auction nears it‚Äôs end the Panda is growing more excited and nervous hoping he will win the auction. At the end of the auction where he wins and a new lil noun appears in the room magically from a bunch of small particles. The lil noun quickly glances over to look at his new lilnoun and they hug.

Talking points (Narration):
‚Ä¢	Every 15 minutes
column4849: a new lil noun is born. The auction is open and anyone can bid. Submit your bid on-chain\n‚Ä¢\tIf someone bids more than you before the auction ends
column4850: your ETH is refunded back to your wallet. You have the option to bid higher.\n‚Ä¢\tIf someone bids in the last minute
column4851: 1 minute is added to the auction time to give everyone an opportunity to send new bids\n‚Ä¢\tAt the end of the auction
column4852: if you have the highest bid
column4853: the lil noun is yours! Settling the auction mints a lil noun to your wallet
column4854:
and begins a new auction

Scene 1 Summary: This demonstrates the lilnoun auction process and briefly highlights the role of a delegate.

Scene 2 [finding the right sort of funding for the project]
The Panda then stretches his legs and walks around the room [while doing a subtle dance] as he makes his way over to his work area in the nounisouri where he has three projects. [these three projects are later used to highlight the most appropriate method for submitting each respective prop] Each project is slightly different
column4855: there is a small project [science fair volcano]
column4856:
a medium project [tbd] and a large project [robot arm]. Panda begins tinkering with the science fair volcano [small project]. It erupts and creates a giant mess! He works some more and fixes it. He pulls out a camera and takes some photos of the volcano and then loads the photos into his computer. He enters a chat window and begins typing. While he is typing he is de-materialized into a bunch of small particles which are then sucked into the computer screen. A fellow lil noun standing nearby reacts to him being sucked in the computer screen and looks over with a quick head jerk[setting changes]. The panda then appears in a gymnasium where we that the room is full of other lil nouns who have their projects on display and are talking with other lil nouns about them/getting feedback. He carries his project over to an open booth and sets it up while he is getting prepared lil nouns come and speak to him to ask him about his project and provide feedback. The scene ends with a shot of the panda shaking hands with another lilnoun. [everything in the scene de-materializes and the panda materializes back to his seat in the nounisouri.

Scene 2 summary: brings up the topic that there are many ways to be funded/the art of choosing the best funding method for your project is an art.

Talking points (Narration):
‚Ä¢	Projects in lilnouns DAO are bucketed into three categories depending on how much funding is needed: small
column4858: you have the option to apply for prophouse funding
column4859: which runs new auctions every 2 weeks. This is usually for projects under 1-2 ETH\n‚Ä¢\tFor medium-sized projects
column4860: applying for small grants is the best route. Small grants can get you up to 10 ETH in funding\n‚Ä¢\tFor large projects that require more than 10 ETH in funding
column4861:
the best route is to go on-chain.

Scene 3 [illustrating prop house/submitting his project for funding using pro]
Now that the Panda has gotten feedback from other lil nouns
column4862: he is ready to submit for funding. The lil noun paces back and forth for a moment and sips his coffee. Then walks over to the computer again. He pulls up the browser window and loads up prophouse. He again is de-materialized into the computer and reappears in a new location - a room full of doorways. Each door representing a different house (lil nouns
column4868: etc.) He walks into the lil nouns prop house and as he walks through the doorway he finds himself in a room that resembles a museum. He then finds a place after being guided there by another lil noun and sets his project up for display. [sets his project down and then presses a remote control that puts a HUD around his project highlighting different features of it. Once he sets up his project
column4869: he begins looking around the museum and voting on other projects he likes. Each time he votes
column4870: a green check mark appears over his shoulder and follows him around as he looks at each project. He finally comes to the end of the museum where he approaches a ballot box. Once he reaches it

[fade out/in] The scene is of a stage where the ones who have one the round of prop house are being celebrated for winning. But unfortunately Panda didn‚Äôt get selected. He walks toward the exit of the museum which is a revolving door and while he pushes himself through the exit
column4872:
the scene de-materializes and the panda re-materializes back in the nounisouri.
Scene 3 Summary: Shows a small project getting funding using prophouse. discusses how small projects would be best directed toward this funding method.

Talking points (Narration):
‚Ä¢	If you have a small project that doesn‚Äôt need a lot of funding

description:"# Buy Noun 235

## **Buy Noun 235**


Noun 235 has been listed for sale onchain to Lil Nouns DAO. The on-chain offer is only executable by Lil Nouns DAO and represents an opportunity for our DAO to acquire its fifth Noun in a trustless transaction. 

We propose Lil Nouns DAO purchase Noun 235 for 99 ETH.

- OS Floor @ Time: 99 ETH
- Moving Average last 7 Auctions: 103.10 ETH
- Moving Average last 30 Auctions: 107.3 ETH
- Note: first Fence head Noun minted on auction

Lil Nouns DAO has indicated that 30% to 60% of treasury is appropriate to allocate towards acquiring Nouns. A temp check for additional treasury spend on Nouns can be found in [Discord](https://discord.com/channels/954142017556979752/966075869674213416/983714239787200523).

So far the treasury has:
- Accumulated ~1373 eth in revenue
- Spent 364.69 eth to purchase 4 Nouns

This puts the DAO at a 28% allocation towards noun acquisitions so far. The purchase of Noun 235 continues our progress towards this goal by increasing our allocation to 33% if passed.


Ask (as represented in the Proposal transaction): Spend 99.00 ETH from the Treasury to purchase Noun #235. 

### **Further Info**

The Collective platform

Core features include: 
Multiple customizable feeds

Easier account management:
 no need for multiple Discourse email/password accounts
column5380:

Community analytics

column5562:
body:"We are finally taking action to get our Nouns delegate process ready for us to vote in NounsDAO proposals! Our scoping document can be found here: [https://www.notion.so/al409/7727ade78b7d4f0289b96ada8e4a6d44?v=08adedaba6f843ee961a441636a245d1](https://www.notion.so/7727ade78b7d4f0289b96ada8e4a6d44)

What am I voting on?

- We have decided to delegate our Noun tokens to a multisig wallet with 5 signers. This group is being coined ‚ÄúLeague of Lil‚Äôs‚Äù and we are asking you to select your top 4 favorite candidates to be selected.
- Keep in mind
column5563: these folks are going to be engaging with our community heavily and the delegate that is selected within this group is going to represent us in token gated NounsDAO channel discussions. We need a strong candidate who is confident and engaged to best represent us in.\n- League of Lil‚Äôs are essentially a steering committee that will collect feedback from our community. Their job is to spark discussion and communicate about important topics/issues within Lil Nouns community and be the liaison between us and NounsDAO.\n- The will be sending out snapshot votes reflecting active NounsDAO proposals. They are responsible for making announcements to the community to participate in snapshot votes
column5564: and then casting the winning vote on the actual NounsDAO proposal on our behalf.\n- Once this group has been decided
column5565: the 5 of them will select the first official Nouns delegate. This delegate is going to be responsible for speaking on our behalf in the NounsDAO discord in their token gated channels.\n- Disclaimer: The elected representatives are subject to term limits
column5566: periodic check in‚Äôs on quality of work with the community to retain their role
column5567:
and will receive a stipend for their efforts which will be decided by the community.

How am I supposed to vote?

- This is a multi select poll in which we are requesting you select your top 4 favorite candidates. Please head over to #election-bios to read everyone‚Äôs submissions!
- To properly vote
column5568:
please click your top 4 favorite candidates and no additional candidates. Each candidate you select will get the quantity of votes that is equal to the number of Lil Noun tokens in your wallet.
    - Example: Al holds 5 lilnouns. Each candidate he selects will get 5 votes each.
    

Good luck candidates!

"
